Sentencas: The effect of the amount of cobalt in (Gd0.6Sr0.4)(0.99)Fe1-xCoxO3- solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathodes (x=0.00, 0.05, 0.10, 0.15, 0.20 and 0.25) was studied by powder X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscopy (SEM), dilatometry, four-point DC conductivity measurements, cone-shaped electrodes, and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Effect of cobalt on the activity of dual phase (Gd0.6Sr0.4)0.99Fe1-xCoxO3- SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: XRD and scanning electron microscopy revealed two phases: a cubic phase and an orthorhombic phase.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt on the activity of dual phase (Gd0.6Sr0.4)0.99Fe1-xCoxO3- SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: One phase has a small particle size (cubic phase), and the other phase (orthorhombic) has a larger particle size.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt on the activity of dual phase (Gd0.6Sr0.4)0.99Fe1-xCoxO3- SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: Dilatometry indicated that the thermal expansion coefficient increased with increasing Co content.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt on the activity of dual phase (Gd0.6Sr0.4)0.99Fe1-xCoxO3- SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity maximum for the Co-rich compound was found to have a value of 82Scm(-1) at approximately 300 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt on the activity of dual phase (Gd0.6Sr0.4)0.99Fe1-xCoxO3- SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: It was shown that the activity of the cathodes was strongly dependent on the amount of cobalt.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt on the activity of dual phase (Gd0.6Sr0.4)0.99Fe1-xCoxO3- SOFC cathodes

Sentencas: The highest activity was found for the cobalt-rich compound (Gd0.6Sr0.4)(0.99)Fe0.75Co0.25O3- with an area-specific resistance of 0.9cm(2) at 600 degrees C, measured on a cone-shaped electrode in air.
Titulo: Effect of cobalt on the activity of dual phase (Gd0.6Sr0.4)0.99Fe1-xCoxO3- SOFC cathodes
